text: The wedge-snouted skink or sharp-lipped mabuya (Trachylepis acutilabris) is a species of skink found in Namibia, Angola, Democratic Republic of the Congo, and South Africa. ==References== Category:Trachylepis Category:Reptiles of Angola Category:Reptiles of the Democratic Republic of the Congo Category:Reptiles of Namibia Category:Reptiles of South Africa Category:Reptiles described in 1862 Category:Taxa named by Wilhelm Peters
title: Trachylepis acutilabris
